features: AUTOMATIC DRAINAGE: This large dish drying rack features an automatic drainage system that consists of a drainboard and a water outlet at the bottom. It can drain excess water into the sink automatically. In addition, the rotatable water outlet is available in 3 directions, so you can adjust the water outlet according to the position of your sink.

LARGE CAPACITY FOR A SMALL KITCHEN: With a practical 2-tier design and a size of 16.5*12.6*12.6 inch, this dish drainer for kitchen counter enables you to store different types and sizes of kitchenware, such as bowls, dishes, knives, wine glasses, kitchen pots, and frying pans. This 2-tier dish drying rack is perfect for families of 3-4 persons.

SPACE SAVING: The top layer of 2 tier dish drying rack can store 14 plates and pots, the bottom layer can keep up to 20 bowls, the side 2 cutlery racks can hold various utensils, one side on holds 5 cups and another side can keep cutting boards. Keep your countertop clean and organized with our 2-tier dish drying rack.

NO TOOLS NEEDED INSTALLATION: The dish rack is easy to install with the attached installation manual and equipped screws.No tools needed!In addition, these accessories can also be quickly disassembled for cleaning. You can simply wipe them with a damp cloth or rinse them under a running tap after use.

RUST-PROOF & SUPER STURDY: The drying rack for kitchen counter is made of high-strength metal which is carefully polished with high-temperature lacquer, ensure that this kitchen organization is anti corrosion and anti-rust,durable and easy to clean which made to last, this kitchen dish rack is a solid metal drying rack choice for every household.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and save space on the counter
reviews.reviewText: I bought this dish drying rack to replace my old one that was taking too much space. This rack is perfect size. It was easy to assembly. Took me about 10 mn to assembly. I really like the drainage system. It helps keep my counter dry. I also like the fact that it has cups holder and the lids holder. The only complaint I have about this rack is that the spoons and knives holder is too small. Overall this is a good product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great drying rack for great price
reviews.reviewText: Great drying rack for the price. Easy to assemble. second tier allows to store more dishes than a regular 1 tier rack. Allows for fast drying and doesn’t not take up lot of space. Very functional. Easy to drain excess water and very easy to clean.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: After using this dish rack for a bit I have a few thoughts about it. First I would like to say I love how easy it is to clean. I would say the water drains out pretty well there are a few spots where it lingers. It has plenty of space and fits while still fitting nicely on the counter top. If I had to change anything it would definitely be the cup drying rack the hooks on the front side. It doesn't stay hooked on the rack well and you can only utilize some of hooks at a time unless you have very slim glassware. All in all It is a good purchase for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great look and functional!
reviews.reviewText: This strainer has an enormous amount of room for all kinds of dishes and is sturdy enough to handle the weight of heavy pots and pans. I like the somewhat industrial/farmhouse look and color. The ONLY improvement I would make is that the lip on the water collector is a little close to the counter level so that if you have a drop-in sink the water doesn’t always drain and remains in the collector. However, slightly tilting the collector solves the problem and there are no leaks on the counter tops.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Went together easily
reviews.reviewText: This was very easy to assemble and is very sturdy. I would have made the bottom tray a little wider and would have gotten rid of the lip, which doesn't really allow for water drainage. It should do the trick though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Very happy with the dish drain. Easy to put together and give great space to my countertop.REMINDER: the drain spot extends so be certain to extend it when you add it on the drain platform.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Made of metal
reviews.reviewText: Excellent quality. Easy to put together. Beat my expectations!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Fits a ton, works great, tho water gets on counter
reviews.reviewText: I’m always amazed at how many dishes this fits! The only downsides are that a number of the elements hang over past the bottom pan, so it does end up dripping on the counter. And the place to hang glasses, glasses end up falling off (but it is perfect for pint plastic containers!). It’s simple to put together and clean and fits my space that has a cabinet right above. I’m glad of this purchase because of how much it holds, I recommend if you’re like me and procrastinate washing dishes.
